A 50-year-old man sustained critical injuries following a three-vehicle collision on the N4 near Ngodwana on Monday March 6. Emer-G-Med’s spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said reports from the scene indicate that a heavy articulated vehicle, a minibus taxi and a light motor vehicle collided on Monday night. ALSO READ: 99 fatal accidents on Mpumalanga’s roads over festive season so far He said a man was critically injured in the crash. He was treated and stabilised by paramedics at the scene before being rushed to a nearby hospital for further care.